# Mandatory Investigation Outputs

Every investigation **must** produce all of the following as **separate `##` sections** in `notes.md`. Each is auto-displayed in the corresponding POD Ticket Dashboard tab. Use `@cases/.template/notes.md` as the scaffold.

## Checklist

- [ ] **Proposed Customer Response** (`## Proposed Customer Response`) — Contains ONLY the customer-facing message body (greeting → explanation → action items → sign-off). **No TL;DR, no summary preamble, no internal notes.** The TSE reviews and adapts before sending — never send without review. Populates POD Ticket Dashboard "Proposed Customer Response" tab.
- [ ] **Zoom Call Preparation** (`## Zoom Call Preparation`) — Use ONLY @templates/customer-communication/zoom-call.md. Populate POD Ticket Dashboard "Zoom Call" tab.
- [ ] **Leadership Summary** (`## Leadership Summary`) — Use ONLY @templates/customer-communication/leadership-summary.md. Populate POD Ticket Dashboard "Leadership Summary" tab. **NON-TECHNICAL audience (managers).** Strict word limits: Leadership Summary ≤45 words, Investigation ≤50 words, Next Steps ≤50 words. No jargon, no config values, no ticket IDs.
- [ ] **TLDR Handover** (`## TLDR Handover`) — Use ONLY @templates/customer-communication/tldr-handover.md. This is a **separate section** from Leadership Summary. It targets TSEs and managers and **CAN include technical detail**. It is Mandatroy to populate the 'TLDR' tab in the Web APP with this section.

## Leadership Summary vs TLDR Handover — They Are DIFFERENT

These are **two separate `##` sections** in `notes.md` with different audiences:

| | `## Leadership Summary` | `## TLDR Handover` |
|---|---|---|
| **Audience** | Non-technical managers triaging | TSEs + managers needing context |
| **Language** | Plain English, no jargon | Technical details welcome |
| **Word limits** | Strict (45/50/50) | No strict limit |
| **Sub-sections** | Leadership Summary, Investigation, Next Steps | Leadership Summary, Investigation, Next Steps, Need from Customer, Important Links |

**Never merge these into one section.** Both must exist independently.

## Rules

- The draft customer response should be ready-to-review, not a rough outline
- Include risk callouts if recommending configuration changes (see `@risk-assessment` rule)
- If more information is needed from the customer, draft a requesting-info message instead of a solution
- Do **NOT** create multiple file variations (`CUSTOMER_MESSAGE.md`, `MESSAGE_SHORT.md`, `SUMMARY.md`, etc.) unless explicitly requested — keep it in `notes.md` and use templates
- **Read the referenced template file before writing each section** — do not write from memory
